A decorated New York police officer was found intoxicated and nearly naked in a random woman’s apartment earlier this month only hours after receiving the department’s second-highest honor.

Four-year NYPD veteran Eugene Donnelly, 27, received the Police Combat Cross June 10 for bravery while off-duty during a shooting. He was then stripped of his gun and shield that evening.

Donnelly, stationed in a Bronx precinct near Fordham University, was so drunk he wandered into the stranger’s apartment wearing only his underwear, sources told the New York Daily News.

