‘He was apparently drinking,’ a police source told the paper. ‘He was celebrating. He went to stay with a friend.’

The officer is believed to have been celebrating in the hours after shaking Mayor Bill de Blasio’s hand while receiving the award in a ceremony at City Hall.

Donnelly was staying at a friend’s apartment in Woodlawn, in the northern Bronx, when he somehow managed to leave the residence and ended up inside the woman’s apartment.

The woman lived in the same building, and police say she accused him of getting into a physical altercation with her, according to the Daily News.

‘He has an encounter with a female, and she claims he roughed her up,’ a police source said. ‘He was in his underwear when this happened.’

